<p style="text-align:justify;">inspection except when the wind is off the Shore or else a dead calm<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  There is nothing Remarkable from the Point to the third and last Bay but the Ruins of a once Magnificent Natural Arch under which Canoes used to pass in full Sail; It is now a confused heap of freestone Slabs which may be had of any dimensions the grit is excellent for Grind Stones<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span></p>
<p style="text-align:justify;">This last Recess is called Minors Bay from Some efforts having been made here as well as in Several other places on the borders of the Lake about Six and thirty years ago to find copper and silver Mines by one Baxter who was employed by the then Duke of Richmond along with Several other Noblemen and Gentlemen<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The enterprize only failed from the villa<span class="DelHand-author">i</span>ny of the person employed who by feeding the Miners on Indian corn and grease and selling them every necessary at an enormous price made a considerable Sum of money<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  The only Revenge in the power of the Workmen was to work as little and as carelessly as they could and even when they found Veins of Metal it is here currently Reported to this day that they concealed them<span class="AddHand-editors">[.]</span>  Such has ever been <span class="AddHand-author">the</span> conduct of the low and ignorant; had they on the contrary done their duty faithfully they would have had it in their power to have brought a Scound<span class="DelHand-author">ai</span><span class="AddHand-author">re</span>l to Justice, and to have</p>

